22/06/2006
ANKARA, Turkey -- Turkish Army head General Hilmi Ozkok reaffirmed his country's support for Albania's bid to join NATO, during a visit to Tirana Wednesday (21 June).
Talks with Albanian President Alfred Moisiu and Prime Minister Sali Berisha focused on bilateral co-operation in the defence sector, and the two sides' commitment to preserving peace, stability and security in the region.
In other news, the 14th session of the Albania-European Commission Consultative Task Force took place in Brussels on Tuesday.
The focus was on electoral reform, property restitution and compensation, freedom of speech and human and minority rights.
(Albanian News - 22/06/06;
Albanian presidential Web site - 21/06/06)
